channel.title: Compiler Issue
channel.description:
Hey Guys,
Lately, whenver I try to compile a newly downloaded source I get a message that says the specified path cannot be reached. I downloaded the latest jdk and everything. Would it have something to do with the contents of the compiler?

item.title: Compiler Issue
item.dc:creator: @Onix Onix
item.description:
@Onix wrote:

Make sure the compiler is directed to a valid jdk path, or you could set up your classpath settings. There are guides on how to do this, and one of the stickied topics in this section has everything to do with compiler related issues.

Read full topic
